76561197961696971,Recommended,263860,12180574,"Posted: 21 September, 2014",all,onehand,"Lovin' the look of this game. Highly recommended if you are really into the pros listed below but are willing to put up with some missing features (in my opinion).PROS:- Awesome minimalist & stylish interface (probably one of my favorites)- Great ambient music and sound effects- Various difficulty levels- Overall very accessible & easy to pick up for an RTS- Games can be as quick or as long as you want them to be depending on map size- Simplified design with abstractions at just the right places while maintaining a strong emphasis on strategy & deep gameplaySuggested improvements:- Keyboard shortcuts -- This is a must for any fast-paced RTS. For example, it would be great to be able to bookmark my shipyard so that I could hit ""1"" then ""A"" to build a battle fleet without having to keep locating it on the map and navigating through the menu to queue a unit.- The ability to set a waypoints or rally points for resulting shipyard production. Oftentimes my shipyards are at least a couple hops away from where I want my forces to end up.- Another player on the forum suggested the ability to see ""at-a-glance"" how well I'm performing in a battle without having to click on the battle itself. This would be extremely helpful in hectic situations where multiple battles are occurring simultaneously.- An at-a-glance display of the number of units of each type currently occupying a system. Instead of having the one icon indicating just the types of units present, there might be two icons if you had for example both a battle fleet and an invasion fleet. Both icons would have their corresponding fleet counts listed. (Or maybe just three counts next to the single icon?) This would be very helpful for quickly planning strategies to amass forces proportionately.Overall though, a game with a lot of promise; it's very easy to sink a bunch of hours in it the way it is.  Keep up the good work devs."
